        -: 1394:/* ---- write_table: .xlsx (Excel) output, dependency-free ------------------
        -: 1395: * An .xlsx file is a ZIP of XML parts. We build the parts as strings and pack
        -: 1396: * them into a STORED (uncompressed) ZIP ourselves, so there is no zlib / CPAN
        -: 1397: * dependency and everything stays in XS. The provenance line (provenance_path)
        -: 1398: * is written into the workbook's document properties as the "comments" field
        -: 1399: * -- dc:description in docProps/core.xml -- mirroring
        -: 1400: *     $workbook->set_properties(comments => comments());
        -: 1401: * from Excel::Writer::XLSX. A numeric-looking cell is written as a number;
        -: 1402: * every other non-empty cell as an inline string. read_table reads it back.
        -: 1403: */
        -: 1404:#define SV_CATLIT(sv, lit) sv_catpvn((sv), "" lit, sizeof(lit) - 1)
