        -: 2171:/* ── parse_formula
        -: 2172: *
        -: 2173: *  Splits "response ~ factor" into two NUL-terminated, heap-allocated
        -: 2174: *  strings.  Leading/trailing whitespace is stripped from each side.
        -: 2175: *  Returns 1 on success, 0 on failure (malformed / missing '~').
        -: 2176: *  Caller must Safefree() both *lhs and *rhs on success. */
        -: 2177:static int
        -: 2178:parse_formula(const char *formula, char **lhs, char **rhs)
