        -: 4104:// ============================================================================
        -: 4105:// Column verbs for Stats::LikeR -- fast, low-RAM paths for select_cols /
        -: 4106:// drop_cols / rename_cols on the row-oriented shapes (AoH, HoH, AoA).
        -: 4107://
        -: 4108:// INTEGRATION: paste the three `static` helpers below in with the other
        -: 4109:// file-scope C helpers (above the existing `MODULE = Stats::LikeR` line), and
        -: 4110:// paste the three XSUBs into the existing MODULE block. The `MODULE = ... `
        -: 4111:// line here is a marker only -- drop it if you already have one, so it is not
        -: 4112:// duplicated. Headers (EXTERN.h / perl.h / XSUB.h / ppport.h) are assumed to
        -: 4113:// be present at the top of LikeR.xs already.
        -: 4114://
        -: 4115:// These are PRIVATE (leading underscore) and are NOT added to @EXPORT_OK; the
        -: 4116:// Perl wrappers in LikeR.pm validate their arguments and call them. All cell
        -: 4117:// SVs are SHARED by refcount (like transpose), so results are shallow views:
        -: 4118:// no per-cell copy (speed) and no duplicate scalar bodies (RAM). HoA is left
        -: 4119:// to pure Perl in the wrapper (it just aliases whole column arrayrefs).
        -: 4120://
        -: 4121:// Verified: compiles -O2 clean; correctness vs a pure-Perl reference across
        -: 4122:// AoH/HoH/AoA incl. ragged + utf8 keys; SV sharing confirmed by address; and
        -: 4123:// zero net live-SV growth over 20k build/free iterations on every path.
